---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Containing V — Top Scoring V Words"
  description="Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing V. Free list of top V words with point values and strategy tips for maximizing your V tile plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing v, v words scrabble, words with v, high scoring v words, scrabble v strategy, scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Containing V — Top Highest-Scoring V Words",
    "description": "Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing V. Complete list with point values and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-v" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring Scrabble word containing V?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "VIVIFY scores 18 points without premium squares. Other high-scoring V words include VORTEX (16 points), SAVVY (14 points), and HEAVY (14 points). V is worth 4 points, making it a solid mid-value tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many V tiles are in a Scrabble bag?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are two V tiles in a standard Scrabble set, each worth 4 points. V can be tricky because there's no valid two-letter word containing V in standard Scrabble dictionaries, making it harder to play in tight positions." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What strategy works best for V tiles in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Pair V with high-value companions like X (VORTEX), Y (SAVVY, HEAVY), or double-V words (VIVID, REVIVE). Since there's no two-letter V word, plan V plays early before the board gets tight. Target premium squares to multiply V's 4-point value." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">More Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Containing V — Top Highest-Scoring V Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        V is worth 4 points and appears on two tiles in the bag. While not the highest-value tile, V presents a unique challenge — there are no valid two-letter V words in standard Scrabble dictionaries. This means you need to plan ahead and use V in longer words before the board tightens. The payoff? Words with double-V like VIVID, REVIVE, and SAVVY score well above average.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 10 Highest-Scoring Words Containing V</h2>
      <p>These are the most valuable words containing V, ranked by base point value. Double-V words and V paired with other high-value letters dominate this list.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VIVIFY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VORTEX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SAVVY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HEAVY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VIVID</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">REVIVE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VELVET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EVOLVE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VALVE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VOWEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why V-Containing Words Require Special Strategy</h2>
      <p>V is the only consonant in Scrabble with no valid two-letter word. This means you can't use the quick-play fallback that tiles like X (AX, EX, OX), Z (ZA, ZO), or J (JO) enjoy. When the board gets crowded, V can become a liability if you haven't planned your play in advance. The key is to use V early in the game while open lanes still exist.</p>
      <p>The silver lining? V pairs beautifully with other mid-to-high value letters. VORTEX combines V with X for 16 points. VIVIFY uses double-V plus F and Y for 18 points. SAVVY and HEAVY leverage V with Y for 14 points each. Words like VIVID, REVIVE, VELVET, and EVOLVE all use double-V to push past 12 points base value. When you draw V, think about pairing it with premium companions rather than trying to dump it cheaply — there's no cheap V dump available anyway.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Play V early:</strong> No two-letter V word exists, so V becomes harder to place as the board fills. Use it in the first half of the game while open lanes remain.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Pair V with high-value tiles:</strong> VORTEX (V+X), VIVIFY (V+F+Y), SAVVY (V+V+Y) — combining V with other premium letters maximizes its scoring potential.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Double-V words are your friends:</strong> VIVID, REVIVE, EVOLVE, VELVET — using both V tiles in one word clears your rack efficiently while scoring well.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>V on premium squares matters more:</strong> Since V has no two-letter shortcut, you need to make each V play count. V on DLS = 8 points; V on TLS = 12 points from one tile.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Consider exchanging late-game V:</strong> If the board is locked and you can't find a V play, exchanging is sometimes correct. V is the hardest consonant to play in tight positions.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing Z — Top Scoring Z Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing K — Top Scoring K Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-w/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing W — Top Scoring W Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
